  "market_context": "Price was in a range between support (~1.08200) and resistance (~1.08270) on the 15M chart. HTF (1H) showed a shift from downtrend to bullish structure with higher highs and higher lows. Price swept sell-side liquidity below equal lows before reversing.",
  "key_observation": "Price swept sell-side liquidity below equal lows (1.08200), then reversed into a demand zone containing FVGs on the 5M chart, confirming a bullish CHoCH and valid long entry opportunity.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the 15-minute analysis timeframe, the analyst identified a range-bound EUR/USD with support at ~1.08200 and resistance at ~1.08270, establishing a bullish bias and targeting only long entries.",
    "Step 2: The analyst identified two liquidity zones: buy-side liquidity at ~1.08270 (above resistance) and sell-side liquidity at ~1.08200 (below support), anticipating price would sweep one before reversal.",
    "Step 3: The analyst switched to the 1-hour higher timeframe and confirmed a bullish market structure shift—higher highs and higher lows after failed breakdown below 1.08020—aligning HTF and LTF bias.",
    "Step 4: The analyst zoomed into the 5-minute entry timeframe and identified two Fair Value Gaps (FVGs) between ~1.08170–1.08200 as the demand zone, noting a bearish imbalance had been resolved after price swept the equal lows.",
    "Step 5: After price swept the sell-side liquidity (equal lows at ~1.08200) and formed a rejection wick, the analyst confirmed a Change of Character (CHoCH) and signaled a long entry at the FVG demand zone with stop loss below the FVGs."
  ],
  "outcome": "Long trade entered after liquidity sweep of equal lows and FVG confirmation; target set at buy-side liquidity (~1.08270).",
  "lessons": "Valid long entries require confluence: HTF bullish structure, liquidity sweep of opposing side, and LTF demand zone (e.g., FVG/Order Block) with reversal confirmation. Sweeping equal lows often precedes strong momentum moves.",
